== English ==
=== Etymology ===
*The term was coined by ''Julián Juderías'' in his ''1914'' book ''La leyenda negra y la verdad histórica'' (''The Black Legend and Historical Truth''). 
=== Noun ===
'''Leyenda Negra'''
*The anti-Hispanic [[Black Legend]] (in Spanish [[Leyenda Negra]]) is the untruthful depiction of [[Spain]] and [[Spaniard]]s as bloodthirsty and cruel, greedy and fanatical with the intention of defaming the country of Spain and its inhabitants, the [[Spanish]] people. The term was later extended to include all [[Hispanic]]s and their countries of origin, in particular the Spanish-speaking countries of [[Latin America]] and their inhabitants. 
